            <title>[JCR-1240] Index segments are only committed on close</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1240</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>There is a check in AbstractIndex.commit(), which prevents that deleted documents are committed to the index. Up to lucene version 2.0 the index was locked when there were pending changes. Beginning with lucene 2.1 this is not true anymore. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-701&quot; title=&quot;Lock-less commits&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;LUCENE-701&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This is a regression of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-788&quot; title=&quot;Upgrade to Lucene 2.2&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-788&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, hence it does not occur in a release but only in trunk.</description>
